<paragraph id="4C48521FB11FFFF266FBF9421161F873" blockId="7.[151,1436,1756,1960]" pageId="7" pageNumber="546">
<taxonomicName id="8BF7299CB11FFFF266FBF94211E5F92F" authorityName="Stocchino &amp; Sluys" authorityYear="2013" box="[151,403,1756,1780]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Dendrocoelidae" genus="Dendrocoelum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="7" pageNumber="546" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="mariae">
<emphasis id="7E838E0DB11FFFF266FBF94211E5F92F" box="[151,403,1756,1780]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="546">Dendrocoelum mariae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found in a spring on the Asinara Island National Park in northern Sardinia (Punta della Scomunica Spring). Animals are usually provided with a pair of eyes, but supernumerary eyes (2-3 on either side) are often present. Moreover, this species is characterized by an adenodactyl that is much larger than the penis papilla and a copulatory apparatus localized far behind the pharynx. The presence of a true sphincter in the terminal tract of the bursal canal is a character shared with the other two Sardinian dendrocoelids (see below) (
<bibRefCitation id="28662FEEB11FFFF26363F8F2117CF873" author="Stocchino, G. A. &amp; Sluys, R. &amp; Marcia, P. &amp; Manconi, R." pageId="7" pageNumber="546" pagination="93 - 112" refId="ref8592" refString="Stocchino, G. A., Sluys, R., Marcia, P. &amp; Manconi, R. (2013 c) Subterranean aquatic planarians of Sardinia, with a discussion on the penial flagellum and the bursal canal sphincter in the genus Dendrocoelum (Platyhelminthes, Tricladida, Dendrocoelidae). Journal of Cave and Karst Studies, 75, 93 - 112. https: // doi. org / 10.4311 / 2011 LSC 0252" type="journal article" year="2013">
Stocchino 
<emphasis id="7E838E0DB11FFFF263E4F8F310DBF873" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="546">et al</emphasis>
., 2013c
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
